View the codebook of a dataset or selected variables.

Source: R/codebook.R
codebook.Rd

codebook() is a function to view the codebook of a dataset or selected variables.

Usage

codebook(.data, ...)

Arguments

.data

The input data (data frame or tibble).

...

<tidy-select> One or more unquoted expressions separated by commas. Variable names can be used as if they were positions in the data frame, so expressions like x:y can be used to select a range of variables. This argument can be omitted.

Value

An object of the same type as .data.

Examples
